pull_request.title: Bug fix: for `dolt_history_` system tables
pull_request.body:
When filtering on an indexed column from the primary index (i.e. a pk column) if a column in the underlying table has been modified and changed its tag in previous versions, we weren't able to create the lookup builder and caused a segfault. This PR changes to use the primary index as a covering index, since it's the closest we have. This is also consistent with [how we had implemented Noms range lookups](https://github.com/dolthub/dolt/blob/1eda29268649a30ae68606f59760959e0a62ed8e/go/libraries/doltcore/sqle/index/index_lookup.go#L86). 

Related to: https://github.com/dolthub/dolt/issues/6891

issue.title: binding variable on `GROUP BY` clause fails when `sql_mode` does not include `only_full_group_by`
issue.body:
Repro in Dolt:
```
mysql> SELECT @@SQL_MODE;
+--------------------------------------------+
| @@SESSION.SQL_MODE                         |
+--------------------------------------------+
| NO_ENGINE_SUBSTITUTION,STRICT_TRANS_TABLES |
+--------------------------------------------+

mysql> PREPARE stmt FROM "SELECT pk DIV ?, SUM(c3) FROM one_pk GROUP BY ? ORDER BY ?";

```

Works on MySQL:
```
mysql> SELECT @@SQL_MODE;
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
| @@SQL_MODE                                                                                         |
+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+

+----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------+
1 row in set (0.01 sec)

mysql> PREPARE stmt FROM "SELECT pk DIV ?, SUM(c3) FROM one_pk GROUP BY ? ORDER BY ?";
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.00 sec)
Statement prepared

mysql> SET @a = 1;
Query OK, 0 rows affected (0.01 sec)

mysql> EXECUTE stmt USING @a, @a, @a;
+----------+---------+
| pk DIV ? | SUM(c3) |
+----------+---------+
|        0 |       2 |
+----------+---------+
1 row in set (0.00 sec)
```


issue.title: Nested subqueries with `EXISTS` and functions / aggregations produce wrong results
issue.body:

Set up:
```sql

CREATE TABLE o (o_id INT PRIMARY KEY, c_id INT, ship TEXT);
INSERT INTO c VALUES (1, 'CA'), (2, 'TX'), (3, 'MA'), (4, 'TX'), (5, NULL), (6, 'FL');
INSERT INTO o VALUES (10, 1, 'CA'), (20, 1, 'CA'), (30, 1, 'CA'), (40, 2, 'CA'), (50, 2, 'TX'), (60, 2, NULL), (70, 4, 'WY'), (80, 4, NULL), (90, 6, 'WA');
```

MySQL results:
```sql
SELECT c_id, bill FROM c AS c2 WHERE EXISTS(SELECT * FROM c WHERE bill=(SELECT max(ship) FROM o WHERE c_id=c2.c_id AND c_id=c.c_id));
+------+------+
| c_id | bill |
+------+------+
|    1 | CA   |
|    2 | TX   |
+------+------+
2 rows in set (0.0013 sec)
```

Dolt results:
```sql
SELECT c_id, bill FROM c AS c2 WHERE EXISTS(SELECT * FROM c WHERE bill=(SELECT max(ship) FROM o WHERE c_id=c2.c_id AND c_id=c.c_id));
+------+------+
| c_id | bill |
+------+------+
| 1    | CA   |
| 2    | TX   |
| 3    | MA   |
| 4    | TX   |
| 5    | NULL |
| 6    | FL   |
+------+------+
6 rows in set (0.00 sec)
```

```sql
+------+------+
```

issue.title: Missing support for `ALL`, `ANY`, and `SOME` operators
issue.body:
Missing support for `ALL`, `ANY`, and `SOME` operators
[MySQL Docs](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/any-in-some-subqueries.html)

Some simple test cases here; there are more skipped tests in `gms/enginetest/queries/lgoic_test_scripts.go`

Set up:
```sql
CREATE TABLE c (c_id INT PRIMARY KEY, bill TEXT);
CREATE TABLE o (o_id INT PRIMARY KEY, c_id INT, ship TEXT);
INSERT INTO c VALUES (1, 'CA'), (2, 'TX'), (3, 'MA'), (4, 'TX'), (5, NULL), (6, 'FL');
INSERT INTO o VALUES (10, 1, 'CA'), (20, 1, 'CA'), (30, 1, 'CA'), (40, 2, 'CA'), (50, 2, 'TX'), (60, 2, NULL), (70, 4, 'WY'), (80, 4, NULL), (90, 6, 'WA');
```

```sql
SELECT * FROM c WHERE bill = ALL(SELECT ship FROM o WHERE o.c_id=c.c_id);
+------+------+
| c_id | bill |
+------+------+
|    1 | CA   |
|    3 | MA   |
|    5 | NULL |
+------+------+
3 rows in set (0.0006 sec)
```

```sql
SELECT * FROM c WHERE bill < ANY(SELECT ship FROM o WHERE o.c_id=c.c_id);
+------+------+
| c_id | bill |
+------+------+
|    4 | TX   |
|    6 | FL   |
+------+------+
2 rows in set (0.0026 sec)
```

```sql
SELECT * FROM c WHERE bill < SOME(SELECT ship FROM o WHERE o.c_id=c.c_id);
+------+------+
| c_id | bill |
+------+------+
|    4 | TX   |
|    6 | FL   |
+------+------+
2 rows in set (0.0026 sec)
```
